author: Matt Walsh
description:
Today on The Matt Walsh Show, it seems that many people have already forgotten about the case of Iryna Zarutska, who was stabbed in the neck by a career criminal on the light rail. But forgetting about her story is exactly what they want. Today, I have an update on the case that makes that clear. Also, have an increasing number of "far-right" young people discovered a new affinity for monarchy? That's what the media is claiming. If it's true, there's a reason for it. I'll explain. And I'm being attacked for saying that intolerance is a virtue. Is that true? Well, obviously it is. I will double and triple down as usual.
